  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether cycling to school is effective in the
      prevention of the metabolic syndrome.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Physical activity plays a crucial role in relation to prevent a clustering of risk factors.
      In adults a lower all-cause mortality has been found in those cycling to work compared to
      inactive commuters. It thus seems possible that cycling to school will entail health
      beneficial effects for children.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
